	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A man has been killed in an apparent hit and run accident on
the N2, outside Riviersonderend, according to Western Cape traffic services. Provincial traffic chief Kenny Africa said a passing
motorist had spotted the body of the man on the side of the road, roughly 23km outside
Riviersonderend, at around 04.30 on Sunday morning. He said the motorist had informed Swellendam traffic
officers that there was a person lying on the shoulder of the road. Africa said officers went to investigate and found the man,
who had died after an apparent hit and run incident. He said the time of the accident was unknown.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  